parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) can lead to reduced vehicle control and increased stopping distances, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The ABS warning light is illuminated on the dashboard
the brakes feel spongy or soft
the vehicle pulls to one side when braking
the brakes make a grinding or screeching noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake vacuum hose can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to reduced braking performance and increased stopping distances, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brakes feel spongy or soft
the brake pedal travels further than usual
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the brakes make a hissing or vacuum-like noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hydraulic clutch hose can cause the clutch pedal to malfunction, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear
the hose is visibly damaged or split.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel line hose can cause a fuel leak, which can lead to a fire hazard, and also cause the vehicle to stall or become inoperable, increasing the risk of accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Strong smell of gasoline when approaching the vehicle
clutch pedal goes straight to the floor
vehicle will not move when pressing the clutch
visible fuel leak underneath the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Clutch Failure Due to Hydraulic System Leak
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system due to a leak can cause the clutch pedal to go straight to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Clutch pedal goes straight to the floor
vehicle will not move when pressing the clutch
visible fluid leak underneath the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty seat belt can fail to restrain the occupant in the event of a crash, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The seat belt fails to lock or tighten when the brakes are applied
the seat belt does not provide adequate restraint during a crash
the seat belt is loose or does not hold the occupant in place.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in a crash can increase the risk of injury or fatality to occupants.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in a crash
airbags fail to deploy despite meeting deployment criteria
occupants experience injuries that could have been mitigated by airbag deployment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the manufacturer and dealer to take responsibility for repairs can lead to delays and increased costs for the owner, potentially leaving the vehicle in an unsafe condition.
symptoms: Manufacturer and dealer dispute over repair responsibility
owner is required to pay for repairs before the manufacturer will take action
insurance company and manufacturer dispute over liability.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An engine compartment fire can cause significant damage to the vehicle, potentially leading to a loss of control, accidents, or injuries. In severe cases, it can also result in fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle's engine compartment is on fire
flames are visible under the hood
smoke is coming from the engine area
the vehicle's temperature gauge is in the red zone
the vehicle's warning lights are illuminated
the vehicle loses power or stalls.
